WEBVTT

00:01.257 --> 00:03.891
Why would the President
want to kill your wife?

00:03.893 --> 00:06.026
Her very existence
is a threat to him.

00:06.028 --> 00:09.964
So, you're telling me, he's so afraid of
a scandal that he would commit murder.

00:09.966 --> 00:11.065
Yes.

00:12.167 --> 00:14.201
This is crazy.

00:14.203 --> 00:17.738
And, assassinating him, how does that
even help you get his bone marrow?

00:17.740 --> 00:19.573
It was the only way
to get near him.

00:19.575 --> 00:24.811
I needed allies, resources, people inside
the White House to help arrange all this.

00:24.813 --> 00:26.646
So, we went to Kincaid's enemies.

00:26.648 --> 00:31.051
They were willing to assist, on the
condition that we guaranteed his death.

00:31.053 --> 00:35.889
And, what about your team?
Archer, Sandrine...

00:35.891 --> 00:37.824
They're what, hired guns?

00:37.826 --> 00:39.225
Do they know all this?

00:41.662 --> 00:43.162
So you lie to them, too.

00:43.164 --> 00:44.898
I told them what
they need to know.

00:44.900 --> 00:48.902
And I suggest you do the same with
your family, especially Brian.

00:48.904 --> 00:51.137
Do you trust how he'll react?

00:51.139 --> 00:53.439
You are out of your mind.

00:53.441 --> 00:56.342
Innocent people are
dead because of you.

00:56.344 --> 00:59.512
I didn't want it to happen
this way, but I'm in too deep.

01:02.516 --> 01:07.053
If I back out now,
they'll get rid of me.

01:07.055 --> 01:10.122
And anybody else who's involved.

01:10.124 --> 01:11.289
My family.

01:12.959 --> 01:14.326
And your family.

01:14.328 --> 01:16.729
You're an FBI agent,
you can make a deal.

01:16.731 --> 01:19.565
Go to the police, the prosecutors,
there's a way out of this.

01:19.567 --> 01:20.699
There isn't.

01:21.801 --> 01:24.036
I can't stop this thing.

01:24.038 --> 01:25.370
And neither can you.

01:27.507 --> 01:29.207
Well, I don't accept that.

01:29.209 --> 01:30.842
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

01:33.579 --> 01:35.580
What if I go to the President?

01:35.582 --> 01:40.118
I'm meeting with his Chief of Staff
tomorrow, I could tell him what's going on.

01:40.120 --> 01:41.953
I don't think so.

01:41.955 --> 01:46.724
The Chief of Staff just died
of a heart attack an hour ago.

01:46.726 --> 01:50.327
(DOOR SLAMMING) The Chief of Staff,
and now Hoffman's dead, too?

01:50.329 --> 01:51.930
Just saw it on the news.

01:51.932 --> 01:55.033
Police believe he was the victim
of an attempted carjacking.

01:55.035 --> 01:58.602
Hoffman I can understand.
He was getting too close to the truth.

01:58.604 --> 02:00.737
But Creasy?
Why'd they take him out?

02:00.739 --> 02:02.440
Creasy was never the boss.

02:02.442 --> 02:05.008
Maybe the people up
the chain got cold feet.

02:05.010 --> 02:07.878
Decided to shut down the operation.
Eliminate loose ends.

02:07.880 --> 02:09.645
If that's true,
why aren't we dead?

02:11.149 --> 02:12.816
The night's still young.

02:12.818 --> 02:15.485
BRIAN: Hoffman's murder
wasn't a coincidence.

02:15.487 --> 02:17.921
I just spoke to the guy,
he knew what was going on.

02:17.923 --> 02:20.624
Duncan and his friends are
nervous and they took him out.

02:20.626 --> 02:22.059
It's possible.

02:22.061 --> 02:24.360
(SCOFFING)
"It's possible"?

02:24.362 --> 02:27.631
Well, I don't think they would
murder a federal agent.

02:27.633 --> 02:28.800
What are you talking about?

02:28.869 --> 02:31.405
They just gunned down
a teenager in our house.

02:31.440 --> 02:33.503
They'll do anything to
get rid of the President.

02:33.505 --> 02:35.732
I have a feeling it's more
complicated than that.

02:35.805 --> 02:37.424
Why?

02:37.508 --> 02:39.709
I just do.

02:39.711 --> 02:41.744
I don't think they're terrorists.

02:41.746 --> 02:44.214
I think there's
something else going on.

02:44.216 --> 02:45.498
This leaves us in a bad spot.

02:45.576 --> 02:47.308
We don't know
who we're dealing with anymore.

02:47.319 --> 02:49.251
Logan's our only partner now.

02:49.253 --> 02:51.621
Partner? I'm not so sure.

02:51.623 --> 02:55.257
I don't like the fact that he didn't
give us a heads up about Hoffman.

02:55.259 --> 02:56.959
Or Creasy.

02:56.961 --> 03:00.129
- It's not a good sign.
- I'm meeting him tomorrow.

03:00.131 --> 03:02.898
- I'll get some answers then.
- Just watch your step.

03:05.201 --> 03:07.869
- Ellen figured it out.
- Excuse me?

03:07.871 --> 03:09.704
Nina.

03:09.706 --> 03:13.808
Her relationship to the President.
The bone marrow.

03:13.810 --> 03:17.379
The more people who know,
the more complicated this becomes.

03:17.381 --> 03:18.547
She's smart.

03:19.749 --> 03:22.216
- She understands that.
- I know she's smart.

03:22.218 --> 03:24.886
But will she keep her mouth shut?

03:24.888 --> 03:27.421
BRIAN: Do you know something
that you're not telling me?

03:27.423 --> 03:30.525
- Like what?
- I don't know. That's why I'm asking.

03:31.927 --> 03:33.995
Do you know why
Duncan is doing this?

03:35.097 --> 03:38.299
No. I have no idea.

03:46.775 --> 03:49.243
MRS. KINCAID:
One of my assistant's was there.

03:49.245 --> 03:52.213
She saw it with her own eyes,
said it was horrible.

03:53.315 --> 03:56.717
Gasping and convulsing...

03:56.719 --> 03:59.586
I can't even think about his
poor wife and their little girl.

04:00.689 --> 04:02.022
It's tragic.

04:02.024 --> 04:03.757
Yeah.

04:03.759 --> 04:06.660
I never cared for Quentin, but...

04:06.662 --> 04:09.731
but any time a young man dies
in the prime of his life...

04:09.770 --> 04:12.128
Like Peter?

04:12.567 --> 04:14.734
Sort of.

04:14.736 --> 04:16.803
What do you mean, "Sort of"?

04:16.805 --> 04:20.940
The truth is, Peter was partially
responsible for his own death.

04:20.942 --> 04:24.211
You think it was Peter's
fault that his plane crashed?

04:24.213 --> 04:27.479
It was his fault that he thought he
was invincible and could fly a plane

04:27.481 --> 04:31.184
over the Rockies, at night, after
20 straight hours of campaigning.

04:31.186 --> 04:34.921
Don't look at me like that.
I loved him as much as you did.

04:34.923 --> 04:37.423
For God's sake,
I practically raised him.

04:37.425 --> 04:40.927
But that doesn't mean we shouldn't
be honest about what happened.

04:40.929 --> 04:42.561
I agree.

04:42.563 --> 04:46.232
The way that my sister compartmentalizes,
and rationalizes, it's...

04:46.234 --> 04:51.203
It's infuriating.
"Peter was too brash, so, he died."

04:51.205 --> 04:53.405
There you go.
As simple as that.

04:53.407 --> 04:55.541
Well, she didn't
want to face the truth.

04:55.543 --> 04:59.111
It's just, I wanted to say to her,
God, I wanted to tell her so badly,

04:59.113 --> 05:02.347
the reason Peter died is because
your husband had him killed.

05:02.349 --> 05:04.616
Well, I'm glad you
restrained yourself.

05:06.452 --> 05:07.986
Here.

05:07.988 --> 05:09.554
It wasn't easy, I swear.

05:11.958 --> 05:13.859
Don't worry.

05:13.861 --> 05:15.593
He'll pay for what he did.

05:17.596 --> 05:19.230
He better.

05:19.232 --> 05:22.333
- Are you losing faith?
- I'm losing patience.

05:22.335 --> 05:24.168
And confidence.

05:24.170 --> 05:27.338
I still have no idea if this
doctor is going to come through

05:27.340 --> 05:30.107
or if the FBI agent
is doing his job.

05:30.109 --> 05:31.842
Vanessa, what are you saying?

05:31.844 --> 05:34.444
I'm saying it's time for
us to get more involved.

